[Current recommendations call for infants as young as 6 months who will be traveling outside of the U.S. to be vaccinated against measles. This recommendation means that parents can begin protecting their children as early as 6 months of age if they have plans to travel internationally. As well as protecting the children, it will restrict entry of measles virus into the US population. - Mod.CP

